{"questionId":"9076655","questionHtml":"<p>The mass of visible matter in the galaxy is <em>M</em>.</p>\n<p>Show that for stars where <em>r </em>&gt; <em>R</em><sub>0</sub> the velocity of orbit is&nbsp;<em>v</em> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {\\frac{{GM}}{r}} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>G</mi>\n        <mi>M</mi>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{m{v^2}}}{r} = \\frac{{GMm}}{{{r^2}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>m</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>r</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>G</mi>\n      <mi>M</mi>\n      <mi>m</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>r</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;and correct rearranging</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076655","referenceCode":"18M.3.HL.TZ1.a","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The mass of visible matter in the galaxy is M. Show that for stars where r > R0 the velocity of orbit is v = G M r .","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option D: Astrophysics","Option D: Astrophysics","Option D: Astrophysics (Additional higher level option topics)","D.5 – Further cosmology (HL only)","Option D: Astrophysics","Option D: Astrophysics (Additional higher level option topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}